      • onSensorError

        void onSensorError(@NonNull
                   SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,
                   @NonNull
                   java.util.Set<java.lang.String> errors)
        Called when an error prevents the sensor from functioning. If the error is resolved the sensor will attempt to reconnect. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.

      • onSensorFailure

        void onSensorFailure(@NonNull
                     SensorDefinition sensorDefinition,
                     @NonNull
                     java.util.Set<java.lang.String> failures)
        Called when a sensor encounters an failure. No further callbacks will be made for this sensor. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.

      • onFailure

        void onFailure(@NonNull
               java.util.Set<java.lang.String> errors)
        Called when the session fails to start or encounters a failure. No further callbacks will be made. Note: The callback will be executed on the original caller's thread.
